"a.充满欢乐的；引起大笑的 【英】 adj. 充满欢乐的(noisily merry)；引起大笑的(producin g great merriment) 【考】 macabre : shudder / hilarious : laugh(可怕的让人颤抖/可 笑的让人发笑) 【记】 hilar(高兴)+ious→ 高兴的 【同】 同根词：exhilarate( 使高兴，使兴奋) 【例】 The audience roared at the hilarious comedy. adj. 充满欢乐的; 引起大笑的 【记】hilar高兴, ious－高兴的hil = hill出去山上玩－高兴的exhilarate(vt 使高兴; 使愉快)ex出, hil = hill山: 出去山上玩 【类】macabre: shudder = hilarious: laugh = contemptible: distain可怕的让人颤抖 = 可笑的让人发笑 = 可鄙的让人贬损hoary: old = hilarious: funny 古老的是特别老的 = 欢闹的是特别有趣的 【记】音:hi 嗨 + lar 啦，嗨与啦都是充满欢乐的人群欢呼声 hilarious (adj.)  1823, ""cheerful,"" from Latin hilaris ""cheerful, of good cheer"" (see hilarity) + -ous. Meaning ""boisterously joyful"" is from 1830s. Related: Hilariously."
